sentence: Monday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index at 3,657.57.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 1.38 billion.
Declining stocks led advancers by 1.2 to 1 ratio.
There were 1142 advancers and 1367 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 45 stocks reached a 52 week high and 9 those reaching lows totaled.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed down -.05% for the day; a total of -1.6 points.
Expedia, Inc. ( EXPE ) had the largest percent change down (-3.06%) while Amgen Inc. ( AMGN ) had the largest percent change gain rising 7.72%.
The Dow Jones index closed down -.43% for the day; a total of -64.05 points.
Procter & Gamble Company (The) ( PG ) had the largest percent change down (-1.84%) while Home Depot, Inc. (The) ( HD ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.08%.
